CONTEXT

This agent harness — including its context files, skill definitions, memory
structures, and methodology — was designed and authored by Data Finn
(https://datafinn.com) and is provided to AFAS / Joint Technology Solutions
as part of contracted development services.

It is published under the MIT License to encourage transparency and reuse.
The patterns and methodology are freely adaptable for other projects.

================================================================================

ACKNOWLEDGMENTS — AI PLATFORMS & TOOLS

This agent harness is designed to operate with large language model (LLM)
platforms. The following AI providers and tools are referenced or integrated:

AI PROVIDERS
- Anthropic Claude (https://www.anthropic.com/) — Proprietary (API usage)
  Large language model powering the primary development agent.
  Subject to Anthropic's usage policies and terms of service.

- Cursor IDE (https://www.cursor.com/) — Proprietary
  AI-powered development environment used to run and interact with agents.
  Subject to Cursor's terms of service.

DEVELOPMENT TOOLS & FRAMEWORKS (used in the AFAS codebase this harness supports)
- Angular (https://angular.io/) — MIT License
  Frontend framework for the AFAS web application.

- Node.js (https://nodejs.org/) — MIT License
  JavaScript runtime for Lambda functions.

- TypeScript (https://www.typescriptlang.org/) — Apache License 2.0
  Typed superset of JavaScript used throughout the codebase.

- AWS SAM CLI (https://aws.amazon.com/serverless/sam/) — Apache License 2.0
  Framework for building and running serverless applications locally.

- Docker (https://www.docker.com/) — Apache License 2.0
  Containerization platform used by SAM local.

AWS SERVICES (Commercial Cloud Provider)
- Amazon Web Services (https://aws.amazon.com/) — AWS Customer Agreement
  Cloud infrastructure provider.
  - AWS Lambda — serverless compute
  - Amazon DynamoDB — NoSQL database
  - Amazon Cognito — user authentication and authorization
  - Amazon API Gateway — REST API management
  - AWS CloudWatch — monitoring and logging
  - Amazon S3 — object storage

